I have spoken to Birch, ONCE in-game prior to this log.  I don't even remember if it was him, but he says I purchased my Lodi shield from him.  I probably did, because I did trade some junk to some random EC tard for my lodi shield.  It was a plesant transaction though.  I made my trade and that was it...  never heard from him in-game again.  <br>
<br>
And then this event takes place...  <br>
<br>
Seriously.  What the heck is this guy's problem?  He comes spouting that line out of nowhere and gets in a verbal duel with me regarding Blight, Krimzin, and my leaving of PO.  <br>
<br>
What the heck is it to you?  Some anti-guild piece of shit sure makes a big deal about the inner goings of guilds and their members.  What is it to you that I left PO.  I didn't want to be in that guild and I wanted to be in another guild, so we parted ways.  Granted, there were some hard feelings... but I did what I felt would make this GAME (yes, it is a game...  this is not real life, nor it is a job...  as long as I don't do anything malicious, I'm pretty sure it's cool.) more enjoyable for myself.  <br>
<br>
Why am I explaining myself?  Who knows...  perhaps to blow off some steam for a totally unnecessary warning against my account.  <br>
<br>
If anyone really cares (which I doubt) I left PO because my REAL LIFE FRIENDS were starting a new guild and I was unhappy with the leadership of my old guild.  It was a difficult decision for me--due to the friends I made in PO.  BUT, at the end, the decision was simple: The game wouldn't be fun for me, if I wasn't battling side-by-side with my buds who I see almost everyday.  <br>
<br>
BTW, I'm tired of seeing all this shit 'bout people using guilds/guild hopping/etc...  Yes, it sucks.  But what can you do?  It's done, move on...  why keep harboring and spreading the hate?  The whining of &quot;we did so-and-so for Ex-Guildmate_01 and he just leaves us.&quot;  Have you thought for a moment that your former guildmate did stuff for you as well?  Do you think that so-and-so should NOT enjoy the game just because you got him some piece of loot?  BTW...  I don't see THIS UBER PIECE OF ARMOR WAS BESTOWED UPON YOU BY YOU GUILD AND YOU OWE IT TO THEM TO LIVE UP TO IT etched anywhere on my BP.  <br>
<br>
If I am not having fun in the game...  I'm either going to 1) Stop playing or 2) Find a way to make it fun.  I'm pretty sure that applies to everyone else...  if they are jus' crawling through the game and doing things just out of obligation, that's a pathetic way to play A FRIGGEN GAME.  <br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong...  I'm all about helping my friends and others do things and get things they want.  I do feel  obligation to my guild to help out and do whatever I can.  I feel that obligation to my friends in the guild cuz I know they will go to bat for me--so I naturally will go to bat for them.  BUT (big but)  I shouldn't feel that they are a ball and chain locked to my ankles.  It's not right to keep doing unenjoyable things just because someone was awarded a nice weapon or armor.  <br>
<br>
That's what some people are making of it...  or at least that's what it sounds to me.  <br>
<br>
I have seen some no-lifer losers in the game--but we have ourselves the grand poo-bah of rejects.  <br>
